<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?The RealmWeaver">The RealmWeaver</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:26 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> What?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=501" TARGET=_self>Re: Wait a minute here...</A> (Koss)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>&gt; Also. Player A is a total jerk, he runs around stealing kills,
<BR>&gt; cursing at everyone, and generally doing everything possible to
<BR>&gt; ruin everyones day. Player B decides to end this annoyance, and
<BR>&gt; is flagged "criminal" for however long.
<P>There is a thing called restraint. Ignore player A and go on with life.
<P>&gt;Forgetting this, he walks into town and gets killed, or a wandering guard
<BR>&gt; comes up while he is resting the criminal flag off and gets
<BR>&gt; killed.
<P>Forgetting this?! If he is unaware enough to FORGET that he is flagged, he deserves to die. Pay attention and you stay alive.
<P>&gt; There are a million ways for you to get killed even with
<BR>&gt; good intentions. Because the game has no way to tell if your
<BR>&gt; intentions were GOOD or BAD. No matter what rules you lay down
<BR>&gt; there will always be exceptions when a good person needs to do
<BR>&gt; something defined as BAD.
<P>Name one. A realistic one. The two above are ridiculous and avoided with the ignore command.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
